      <body>On 3.0 is working that way.
It's automatically escaped because you start with a SafeBuffer and the output builder concat with the SafeBuffer he manages using this method from SafeBuffer

    module ActiveSupport #:nodoc:
      class SafeBuffer &lt; String
        def concat(value)
          if value.html_safe?
            super(value)
          else
            super(ERB::Util.h(value))
          end
        end
        alias &lt;&lt; concat
      end
    end

What thing you're saying that's not working?
Did you try the latest version of 2-3-stable with http://github.com/rails/rails_xss</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;On 3.0 is working that way.&lt;br&gt;
It's automatically escaped because you start with a SafeBuffer and
the output builder concat with the SafeBuffer he manages using this
method from SafeBuffer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code&gt;module ActiveSupport #:nodoc:
  class SafeBuffer &amp;lt; String
    def concat(value)
      if value.html_safe?
        super(value)
      else
        super(ERB::Util.h(value))
      end
    end
    alias &amp;lt;&amp;lt; concat
  end
end&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What thing you're saying that's not working?&lt;br&gt;
Did you try the latest version of 2-3-stable with &lt;a href=
&quot;http://github.com/rails/rails_xss&quot;&gt;http://github.com/rails/rails_xss&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
